  <li>For the dressing, put the lemon juice, half the zest, honey, soy sauce, mustard and oil into a small jar. Seal the lid, give it a quick shake, season and put aside until needed.</li>
  <li>Using a mandolin or sharp knife, thinly slice the zucchini, then cut the snowpeas into thin strips and put the vegetables into a salad bowl.</li>
  <li>Mix in the parmesan, nuts, herbs and dressing, season again and top with remaining lemon zest.</li>
</ol>
